		<title>03TRANSPORT SOUTH OF BARRHEAD</title>
		<content> Public transport does not exist within
 the area and the people living within 
 it (mostly farmers and farmworkers)   
 must rely on their own transport at   
 least as far as{Barrhead, Neilston or 
{Newton Mearns.}                       
                                       
 All three of these centres give access
 to{British Rail}stations and{Bus      
{routes}with  services to{GLASGOW.     
                                       
 In addition{Barrhead and Newton Mearns
 have bus services to{KILMARNOCK}and   
 beyond to the{AYRSHIRE COAST.}        
                                       
{Barrhead}also has a bus service to{   
{PAISLEY.}                             
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       </content>
